On Fri, 28 Jul 2000, Jamie Lokier wrote:
>They don't tell you how much space is actually used.  However I fail to
>see why i_blocks is not good enough.
For example some fs (like reiserfs) can not allocate a full block for
files smaller than blocksize (so if you'll use i_blocks you'll overstimate
the disk usage).
